Air Temp: 12 degC. Wind Speed: 10 km/h. Wind Dir. N. Waves: 0.2m. Wind calmed close to 1 pm. -- Light wind and no boats on the lake. Cormorants. 4 inches of rain over lsat couple of days. Hit bottom and rinsed 10 times. evan is an ecology student at u of c 3rd year. Had evan help with the sampling. 1 haul per site and 7 m at profile. Great blue heron. Hit bottom on second site as well.

Air Temp: 13 degC; wind speed, 6-13-25 km/h; wind dir, NW; waves, 0.2-0.5 -- Light wind, mussel sample at dock, wind pickup through day, 3 boats on water, particles in water but good clarity, pelicans, cormorants, loons, boat inspection station at the lake when we pulled boat out. Lots of people on water in pm; Micocystin, M180224

Air Temp: 16 degC; Wind speed: 0-5 km/h; wind dir, SW; -- Calm, pelicans present, fish jumping, snails on substrate sampler, partuckes in water and streaks on surface, busy boat launch; Microcystin, M180223
Air Temp: 9 degC, Wind Speed 6-9 km/h, Wind Direction SE, WV 0.2 -- smoke. light rain. stopped. sunshine. new location for deep spot; microcystin M180222
Missed trip due to unsafe weather.
Discrete metal handgrab at 0.5m

Air Temp: 14 degC. Wind Speed: 5 km/h. Wind Dir. NW. Waves: 0 m. -- Depth on probe was not reading properly, used tape measurer to determine probe depth and input by hand afterwards. Zoo tow was done at 2.4 km/h for 30 seconds = 19 m. Franklin gulls and loons. -- Microcystin M180252.

Air Temp: 27 degC, Wind Speed 2 km/h, Wind Direction N, Waves 0, NET tow, MICROCYSTIN M180251 -- No profile taken, as surveyor died. Surface bloom at Jenny and Derk's dock (Anita's neighbors). Cyano bloom and/or streaks on water present on the whole lake. Today hot and calm. Lots of waterfowl on lake. Cows in field nearby seem to have access to go directly to lake. Derk said cyano blooms not typical for the lake. Also mentioned dairy farm, pig farm and agriculture near lake. N.B. zoo haul = 2x 1m vert haul

Air Temp: 21 degC, Wind Speed 9 km/h, Wind Direction N, Waves 0.1, NET tow, MICROCYSTIN M180250 -- Lots of algae, some aphanizomanin- bloom and streaks at dock, Zoop haul 1.5m x2, did grab samples for composite- saw cows (3) in field with access to drink from lake

Air Temp: 13 degC, Wind Speed 7 km/h, Wind Direction N, Waves 0.03, MICROCYSTIN M180249, NET tow -- Overcast day, some light rain while sampling. Still come cyano bloom at dock and some streaks on lake. Aphanizominin present/particles floating. Green "clumps" floating around as well. No cows on shore today.

Air Temp: 7 degC, Wind Speed 5 km/h, Wind Direction N, Waves 0.01, MC M180248, NET tow -- Started to rain part way through day, water level low, ~ CAGO on water, Sonde depth calibration doesn't vary strongly (ie. lm check depth said 0.88m)
Wind 15 km/hr out of the N, coordinates: 54.6328 -110.5193

Winds 5-10 km/hr out of NW, waves 0.05m. Used L5 Well Pad access, calm clear day with no visible alage at profile site. Lily pads and macrophytes in shallows. Used Auto chart to grid the N basin, Tyrone joined for sample. 4-5 other boats on lake, lots of operators came to talk to us about fishery questions and reported dropping water levels.
Calm, no wind
Wind 10 km/hr out of SE, waves 0.10 m

Station: BUFFALO LAKE (NEAR BASHAW), MAIN BASIN COMPOSITE
SampleComment: GPS: 52'28, 112'51. Air Temp: 17 degC to 26 degC by end of sampling. Wind Speed: 7 km/h. Wind Dir: SW. Waves: 0.05 m. -- Calm day. No other boaters..typically busy on weekends. Lots of development around lake. Lots of waterfowl, pelicans especially. Muddy bottom (~20 cm). Rich development on west side. Lots of beaver dams on the north shore. -- Microcystin: M180242.

Station: BUFFALO LAKE (NEAR BASHAW), MAIN BASIN COMPOSITE
SampleComment: GPS: 52.47176, 112.85839, Air Temp: 15 degC, Wind Speed 13 km/h, Wind Direction NW, Waves 0.15, NET tow, MICROCYST M180241 -- Lots of windy storms recently, foam on top of the lake.Not much wind, very cloudy, clay bottom, starting spitting rain while sampling. Buffalo Lake touches 3 different counties, according to Richard, a pipeline goes underneath NW part of lake near golf course. Small outlet (tail creek), but mostly water evaporates out. RV develompent currently 100 lots. to increase up to 700 in next few years. Probably increase in boat traffis on lake

Station: BUFFALO LAKE (NEAR BASHAW), MAIN BASIN COMPOSITE
SampleComment: GPS: 52.47175, 112.85812. Air Temp: 29 degC, Wind Speed 12 km/h, Wind Direction SW, %C 0 (still smoke), Waves 0.3, NET tow, MICROCYSTIN M180240 -- Started with composite samples at *;36 MST. Secchi at site "1366" was 1.4m Did profile at 9:50 MST. Recent storms past week but not in last 3 days. out with richard Gaffeney, Chris P, Bryan

Station: BUFFALO LAKE (NEAR BASHAW), MAIN BASIN COMPOSITE
SampleComment: GPS: 52.47183, 112.85809. Air Temp: 17 degC, Wind Speed 7 km/h, Wind Direction SW, 100% smoke, Waves 0.1, NET tow, MICROCYSTIN M180239 -- Lots of smoke recently. RV development already seeing lots more trailers (more estimated 200). Week days almost no boats on lake (~5-10 fishing). Weekends very busy and lots of recreational boating. No rain in past few weeks, lots of smoke.

Station: BUFFALO LAKE (NEAR BASHAW), MAIN BASIN COMPOSITE
SampleComment: Composite sample was not collected due to wind, waves, and incoming storm. Drifted during the profile - quality of profile is questionable. Trip was not rescheduled. ORP was ommitted as it was not functioning properly after the previous lake sample that day.

SampleComment: GPS: 52'46.843, 112'58.717. Air Temp: 17degC. Wind Speed: 5 km/h. Wind Dir. SW. Waves: 0.02 m. -- Couldn't find the 18 m profile site - because dark clouds we took 13 m which was the depeest we could find. No other boaters today. Quiet before the storm. Lots of cabins on lake front. It was raining a bit when first arrived - not much rain during sampling. -- M180257.

GPS: 51.99138, 114.87893, Air Temp: 28 degC, Wind Speed 5 km/h, Wind Direction SE, Waves 0-0.2, NET tow, MICROCYST M180256 -- Hot day! 2 other boaters fishing, 2 tubing. profile depth may be off +/- 20cm as I noticed 1m check not in line with mark on cord. Had some issues with probe connection- fixed after unplugging and replugging probe & surveyor. Boat traffic on lake increases to around 20 boats on wekends. Harold, mayor of summer villiage, noticed increased turbidity at docks along shore on weekend.

GPS: 51.99170, 114.87674, Air Temp 20degC, Wind Speed 10 km/h, Wind Direction SW, Waves 0.01, NET tow, MICROCYST M180255 -- profile +- 10 cm (based off 1m check. not sure if depth is calibrating properly). 5 other boats fishing.  did profile at deeper spot- al clark, volunteer, helped finding the spot. small shower last night (~2mm).

GPS: 51.99057, 114.87778, Air Temp: 10 degC, Wind Speed 0, Wind Direction 0, Cloud 0% BUT SMOKE, Waves 0, NET tow, MICROCYST M180254 -- Took profile at GPS point 1376. sampling depth 10m (euphotic depth 12.4). Profile depth of 0.1m (calibration didn't hold well). Lots of boaters for fishing and recreation. Some residents own new "wake boats" according to Al Clark. These create especially large wakes for surfing and wakeboarding.  Typically stay on SW end of lake (away from summer village). there is a speed limit near shore l6ibin residences.

GPS: 51.99147, 114.87932, Air Temp: 3 degC, Wind Speed 7 km/h, Wind Direction SW, Waves 0.05, NET tow, MICROCYSTIN M180253 -- Very cold morning, drifted a bit on profile. Many residents are not full time residents and leave some time in september. Notice lm check depth said 0.88m. One other boat fishing near profile.

GPS: 55'13.3, W113'17.1. Air Temp: 15 degC. Wind Speed: 7 km/h. Wind Dir: n/a. Waves: 0.05 m. -- Nice calm day. 8 am start. No boaters in sight. Last year algae bloom - water was blue. Forest Fires and Forestry station helicopters in the area. Big storm and wind last week made the wtaer brackish/brown. Cabins around lake, lots of fishing, public beaches too. Leak on motor - oil would be visible when we stopped to sample. -- Microcystin M180120

GPS: 55.22272, -113.28564. Air Temp: 20 degC. Wind Speed 11 km/h (up to 24). Wind Direction: SE. Waves: 0.2 m. Tow net. Calm day - 2 other boaters. Windy over the weekend and 2 weeks ago had a massive wind storm. Cyano particles round floating, as well as other curve shaped algae (likely aphanizomenon). - Microcystin ID M180119.

GPS: 55.22483, 113.29526, Air Temp: 15 degC,  Wind Speed 10 km/h, Wind Direction SE, Waves 0.4, NET tow, MICROCYST M180118 -- Lots of smoke recently because of forest fires. Yesterday very smoky, today is not bad. Surveyor died at 1m check. lots of aphanizominin. South end of lake lots of algae clumps floating near surface.

GPS: 55.22303, 113.28872, Air Temp: 10 degC, Wind Speed 7 km/h, Wind Direction S, Waves 0.3, NET tow, MICROCYST M180116 -- Rainy day, no other boats out. Lots of residents take their boats and docks out on sept long weekend. Lake still quite green. Lots of aphanizominin floating around as well as green "clumps". During zoop haul, brown film was in paster-not sure if this is a specific type of algae or sediment.
Bottom substrate is visable. Euphotic zone is greater than depth.
Lots of swimmers and paddlers today. Bottom substrate visable throughout lake.
Bottom substrate visable throughout the lake.  Gusty west wind.
Bottom of lake is visable.  Cool and calm

GPS: n/a. Air Temp: 14 degC. Wind Speed: ~25 km/h. Wind Dir: SE. Waves: 0.3 m. -- Very windy and overcast in the a.m. Concrete and cables at the bottom of the lake for divers - lake has lots of runoff in the spring - lots of wetlands in catchement and farmers. Water very clear. Public beach on shore. Lots of new houses on lakefront. 2 boats out fishing. Drifted lots while taking profile - potential damage to probe.

GPS: 52.46033, -110.36545. Air temp: 15 degC. Wind Speed 13 km/hr. Wind Direction: NE. Waves: 0.1 m. -- Hail storm in wainwright last night. At lake 8 mm rain. Slight wind, dark clouds but no rain during sampling. 1 other boater fishing. Choppy water for comp. Historically, people brought sand in truckloads and dumped since and let sink. Wanted a sandy bottom to the lake. -- Microcystin ID M 180124

GPS: 52.76697, -110.60854. Air Temp: 26 degC. Wind Speed 5 km/hr. Wind Direction: NW. Waves: 0. -- Gorgeous day. It's been very hot the past week. Yesterday had a big storm out at 7 am. Rain lasted 10 minutes and maybe left 8 mm. Weekends are busy with boat traffic (20-25 boats). Many waterskiers and 1 wakeboarder. Did the profile slightly to the east and found a deeper spot than usual. -- Microcystin M180123

GPS 52.76722, -110.60906. Air Temp: 15 degC. Wind Speed 7 km/h. Wind Direction NW. Waves 0.1 m. -- Volunteer mentioned bloom and smell east of the boat launch. Did 01 and 0.5 twice had to redo bc drifted. Small white particles floating just below the surface in between sampling periods like dandruff. -- Microcystin M180122. Tow net.
GPS: 52.76717, -110.6088. Air Temp: 10 degC. Wind Speed 7 km/h. Wind Dir. N. Waves: 0.05 m. -- Rainy day. No other boaters. Many residents take boats and docks out this month. -- M180121. Tow net.

SampleComment: GPS: 53.46083, -113.0908. Air Temp: 18degC. Wind Speed: 10 km/h. Wind Direction: NE. Waves: 0.05 m. -- No traffic on lake. Water fairly turbid. Water is higher than normal. DO was not reading well @ 0.1 m, went to 0 then bounced to 600% sat. -- Microcystin M180084.

GPS: 53.46083, -113.09080. Air Temp: 18 degC. Wind Speed: 15 km/h. Wind Dir. SE. %Cloud: 70%. Waves: 0.05 m. -- Installed substrate sampler at richard's dock. One ski boat - wind picked up at 9:50. AIS Waypoints: hal1a Hal2 Hal3. Grab sampled for composite water at 0.5 m depth. County AIS substrate sampler is also installed at Richard's dock. Checked and no mussels. Tow Net. Microcystin ID M180085.

GPS 53.46083 -113.0908. Air Temp: 22 degC. Wind Speed: 5 km/h. Wind Dir. NW. Waves: 0. -- w north sask limno crew> Christopher, laura, and vanessa. 2 pelicans, 6 geese on beach, lots of grebes. Couple of water skiers out on the lake. -- Microcystin ID M180086.

GPS 53.46083, -113.0908. Air Temp: 15 degC. Wind Speed 20 kmh. Wind Dir: E. Waves: 0.3 Cold and windy. lake is high. lake using sounds to scare away geese. Volunteer has observed sediment in the lake. Volunteer thinks pH might be the dropping. Microcystin ID M: 180087.

SampleComment: GPS: 54.51833, -110.42778. Air Temp: 10 degC. Wind Speed: 6 km/h. Wind Dir. W. Wind increased to 13 km/h @ 11:30. Waves: 0-0.05 m. -- Kirk provided access to boat launch, NRPK at the dock ~20 cm in diamter in 50 cm of water. Calm wind, thick mosquitoes, using aqua map and wind finder apps. Sun coming out, loons, grebes, geese. Kirk indicated 6 inches of rain the last 3 days, very strong winds last few days. Shona lost tape measure and weight. Maple flag ongoing - noisy. Used 5 m of tubing and one haul per site. Water has moved into the trees, forest tent caterpillars have devastated trees beyond the shoreline.-- Microcystin M180092

GPS: 54.51833, -110.42778. Air Temp: 15 degC. Wind Speed: 5 km/h. Wind Dir: SE. Waves: 0 m. Calm, good water clarity, no botas on the lake, few particles in the water (pollen yellow) young of the year fish schooling at water's surface at almost all wq sites. pelican, bald eagle, jets flying over, loons. Pollen down 0.5 m in water column. -- Microcystin ID:M 180091.
GPS: 54.5183, -110.428. Air Temp: 20 degC. Wind Speed: 4-5 km/h. Wind Dir: SW. Waves: 0m. -- Rain at the start of sampling them clearing at 15.45. ~ 1 mm. Microcystin ID: M180090.

GPS: 54.5183, -110.428. Air Temp: 14 degC. Wind Speed: 0-10 km/h. Wind Dir: NE. Waves: 0.1. --- Loons smokey conditions, DO probe not working, calibration failed in the field. calibrated yesterday and it was successful. But storage cup disintegrated! Replaced yesterday. Total phosphorus QC done under the name Lake 12. Sand particles in zooplankton hauls. Tow Net. -- Microcystin ID M: 180089.

GPS: 54.5183. -110.428. Air Temp: 9 degC. Wind Speed 0-5 km/h. Wind Dir. W. Waves: 0.1m. Tow Net. -- Light wind, overcast, no boats, Esso sampling wq at 1:00. as per discussion with Kellie. - Microcystin ID: M180088.
DO probe not working
Discrete metal handgrab at 0.5m
Top/ Surface sample at 2.0 m depth due to ice thickness. Discrete samples, top, mid and bottom, at 2.0 m, 4.0 m, and 6.0 m. Surface Field Blank named Meander Lake for metals and Hg.
all parameters collected at 4.0 m
Bottom sample at 6.0 m depth using perisaltic pump.
Alot of Aphan at profile site.Wiscon net used for zooplankton
Calm, cloudy, lots of aphan in the water.  Tow net used for Zooplankton and veligers
Smoky haze from BC fires.  Zooplankton and veliger collected with tow net.  Thick mats of algae on east side of lake
Lots of snow and precip in the last week.  Lots of aphan still in the water

Air Temp: 20 degC. Wind Speed: 15 km/h. Wind Direction: NE. Waves: 0.05 m. Lots of cottages. New developments planned. Houses near site 9 have cleared all vegetarion from water front. We drifted out of the 9 m depth as profile was taken. There is a 60 ft drop off near site 4. 2 other boats on the lake and some divers. Lots of boats docked. Muddy bottom that just keeps sinking. Jocelyn is very keen on learning about what we measure and limnology. Samples were collected at 3 m instead of 3.8 m for the composite by accident. -- Microcystin M180076

GPS: 53.47917, -114.25556. Air Temp: 15 degC. Wind Speed: nil. Wind Direction: none. Waves: 0. -- Water leaked out of probe cup during storage. Probe was damp but not saturated. can see some fine particles on top of th ewater. Pollen? sediment? Big wind on weekend with whitecaps. Boat swung a bit during profile so depth was a bit shorter than expected. 8.9 m depth may be in a narrow pocked. Microcystin ID: M180077.

GPS: 53.47917, -114.25556. Air Temp: 14 degC. Wind Speed 10 km/h. Wind Direction SW. Waves: 0.05 m. -- No boats. Light rain on and off throughout sampling. Wind gusts up to 15 km/h and on and off with rain. 5 loons, 2 juveniles -- were fishing. 5 pelicans near site 7 north end of th elake. One TP QC sample taken under lake name lake 13. -- Microcystin ID M180078. Tow net.
Missed Trip - Weather

GPS: 54.25944, -110.74472. Air Temp: 30 degC. Wind Speed: 1-2 km/h. Wind Direction: 1-2 km/h. %Cloud: 5%. Waves: 0 m. -- Calm and hot, lake flooded to road way, SW walking path flooded. Lots of waterfowl. Tried to find 4 m depth, no luck. Paul mentioned 2 years ago he watched a deer walk across the lake. Depth sounded found 1.5m. Very hot, mosquitoes. Zoo haul at 1 min @ 0.8 km;hr. Depths not over 1.8 m but hard bottom, not silty. Saw grebes and babies. Particles in water. Parked left side SW corner to launch. Wind picked up to 5 km/h causing waves at 0.05 m. Noticeable algae growth on northeast side by bridge: stringy with red zooplankton very thick. -- Microcystin M180235

GPS: 54.25944, -110.74472. Air Temp: 31-33 degC. Wind Speed 6-10 km/h. Wind Direction: W. Waves: 0. -- Light wind, deployed substrate sampler at the bridge by food. NE very green, algae clumps plus grass clippings. on south side clear water. zooplankton red. Tow net. Microcystin ID M180234.

GPS: 54.25944, -110.74472. Air Temp: 28 degC. Wind Speed: 15-20 km/h. Wind Direction: W. Waves: 0.2-0.3 m. White caps, water qulaity looked good. Strands of algae present. Forgot to collect 3rd mussel sample (missed). Tow net. Microcystin ID M180233.

GPS: 54.25944, -110.74472. Air Temp: 15 degC. Wind Speed: 6-11 km/h. Wind Dir: SW. Waves: 0.2 m. -- paul and Karen sampling, foul odour onl yon east side of lake from the bridge. Nostoc clumps on south side. Sample retained. Microcystin ID M. 180232. Tow net.

GPS: 54.25944, -110.74472. Air Temp: 9 degC. Wind Speed: 0-5 km/h. Wind Direction: NE. Waves: 0m. -- Calm cool evenings, lots of coots, thick aquatic vegetation. 3 muskrats at launch area. -- Microcystin ID M. 180231.
Discrete metal handgrab at 0.5m

SampleComment: GPS: 53.71667. -114.5. Air Temp: 18 degC. Wind Speed: 8 km/h. Wind Dir: W. Waves: NA. -- Long thin algae and round green coloured globular algae.Lake is calm and not busy. DO keeps cutting out. Bouncing around at 0.1 and 0.5 m readings. -- Microcystin M180072.

Station: LAC STE. ANNE, WEST SIDE COMPOSITE
SampleComment: GPS: 53.71667. -114.5. Air Temp: 25degC. Wind Speed nil to 2 km/h. Wind Dir: W. Waves: 0. Lots of weeds at boat launch. lots of dispersed aphanizomenon in wtaer column. Installed AIS substrates at boat launch. Bridget meeting today with alberta environment to talk about pesticide application on lake isle. The pesticide application is planned for tomorrow July 18. Tow net. Sampled with orlando and his 2 daughters laurel and abby. Microcystin ID: M180073.

Station: LAC STE. ANNE, WEST SIDE COMPOSITE
SampleComment: GPS 53.71667, -114.5. Air Temp: 18 degC. Wind Speed: 5 km/h. Wind Direction: W. Waves: 0.05 m. -- Arrowhead growing at boat dock. very smokey sky - blocking out sun quite a bit and cooling off air. Suspended algae grass clippings very dispersed. North eastern most site algae was very dense in the wtaer column. Orlando sebastien and alvin sampling. Western most site lgae cleared and lots of zooplankton visible in the water column. Whole bunch of floating snails at the site on NW side of island. Hit bottom and pulled probe so redox was funky at 7.0 m. Tow net. Mirocystin ID: M180074.

Station: LAC STE. ANNE, WEST SIDE COMPOSITE
SampleComment: GPS: 53.71667. -114.5. Air Temp: 10 degC. Wind Speed: nil. Wind Direction: nil. Waves: 0 m. -- Elaise, Alvin, and Jordan, and Orlando sampling. Lots of gulls on lake. Suspended algae at boat launch and streaking algae into west basin and clumping on easternmost portion of west basin. Microcystin ID: M180075. Tow net.

SampleComment: GPS: 52.43321 -113.79774. Air Temp: 19 degC. Wind Speed: 10 km/h. Wind Dir: SW. Waves: 0.05 m. -- Quiet day, no other boaters on the lake. Plant o build education centre on the lake. No bottom depth bc no guard on probe. -- Microcystin M180105.

GPS: 52.43321 -113.79774. Air Temp: 24 degC. Wind Speed: 19 km/h. Wind Dir: NW. Waves: 0.3 m. - a bit windy in n basin side of lake. No other boaters. Hard substrate attached on rowing club dock. Composite sample depth 1.5 instead of 2.8. Microcystin ID M 180266. Tow net.

GPS 52.43321, -113.79774. Air Temp: 13 degC. Wind Speed: 5 km/h. Wind Direction: SE. Waves: 0.05 m. -- Cloudy day. Lots of aquatic plants across most of the lake. N end is very very shallow (haul 0.10 m.) Andy from the central alberta rowing club is concerned about plants near their dock. he has noticed different plants this year (possibly arrowhead). At a glance there is arrowhead, milfoil, lilies, attail, grass, pondweed, and new plant (young lily?) Fry's pondweed, and richardson's pondweed. Microcystin ID: M180265. Tow net.

GPS: 52.43267, -113.79825. Air Temp: 7 degC. Wind Speed: 4 km/h. Wind Direction: NW. Waves: 0. Cloudy day. Had snow last week and rain in the past few days. wtaer levels are very low (2 meter land stretch between water and old water line at Bill and Griseldas. Rowing club has difficulty rowing because of all the aquatic plants at the bottom. Anto and watershed want to meet with lacombe County to talk about water levels. Probe depth off - (at 1 m surveryor read 0.94 m.).

Each site 2 hauls only collected 6 mx 2 at profile site. -- Microcystin M180102.

GPS: 53.85889, -110.50917. Air Temp: 14 degC. Wind Speed: 5-10 km/h. Wind Direction: S. Waves: 0.1 m. -- Rain just passed, algae blooms present, substrate sampler deployed at Bev's dock. 2 boats on the lake. Very green. Calm winds after profile site. -- microcystin Id: M180101. Wisconsin Net.

GPS: 53.85889, -110.509174,  Air Temp: 20 degC. Wind Speed: 2-6 km/h. Wind Direction: N. Waves: 0. -- Blue green algae prominent at bev's dock 4 days ago.Cleared up now for 2 days. Duckweed at profile site, rain and sunshine. Microcystin ID M: 180100. Tow net.

GPS: 53.85889, -110.50917. Air Temp: 25 degC. Wind Speed: 13 km/h. Wind Dir: W. Waves: 5-10 cm. -- Clear skys, BC smoke, brad sampling with bev and shona. Weird floating algae clumps on surface - took a grab sample - looks like oscillatoria possibly? Tow net. Microcystin ID M: 180099.
GPS: 53.85889, -110.50917. Air Temp: 8 degC. Wind Speed: 0-5 km/h. Wind Direction: SW. -- Light wind, sunny, green particles in the water, cormorants. -- Microcystin ID M180098. Tow net.

Furthest site N near bullrush too many weeds to get all the way there. historical 2 saw mills and gravel washing. landfill nearby and sewage lagoons. -- Microcystin M180110.

GPS: 52.77021, -112.98049. Air Temp: 19 degC. Wind Speed: 30 km/h. Wind Direction: NA. %Cloud: 0%. Waves: 0. -- Lots of cyanonear dock very thick. present on whole lake. lots of wees along the shore. GPS: 52.77041. -112.98062. Air Temp: 20 degC. Wind Speed: 9 km/h. Wind Direction: SE. %Cloud: 5%. Waves: 0.05 m. -- Lots of aphanizomenon, but no surface bloom, some streaks on water in areas near dock. pectonatus grew all the way across the lake  (w to E) near site 2 on map. didn't do site 4 on very N end of lake because of weeds. Microcystin ID M 180106. Tow Net.

GPS: 52.76939. -112.97984. Air Temp: 10 degC. Wind Speed: 8 km/h. Wind Direction: S. %Cloud: 0. Waves: 0.10 m. -- Water level is lowest since 2002. Water is still very green, aphanizomenon and other algae).3 spots on N end, covered in aquatic plants. Cant access very N site in weeds. Did hand grabs for comp. doug mentioned that weeds on N end across the whole lake is normal (not caused by drop in water levels). Microcystin ID: M180107. Tow net.

GPS: 54.28333, -115.65833, Air Tem: 5 degC. Wind Speed 8 km/h. Wind Direction: NW. Waves: 0.01m. -- Few globs of floating algae at profile site. 1 fishing boat. 20 gulls on boat launch dock with lots of poop on dock. heard 1 loon. -- Micorcystin ID M180180. Tow net.

SampleComment: GPS: 52.43787, 113.79353. Air Temp: 15 degC. Wind Speed: 7 km/h. Wind Direction: N. %Cloud: 50-70 %. Waves: 0.1 m. -- Quiet lake - max speed is 12 km;h. 1 other boat. water levels low (dock isn't quite in wtaer). Lots of campers. rain cloudsa bove. Depth sounder didn't work so used the one on Jim's boat. Red daphnia in zoop haul as well as clear green ones. Composite only had 8 sites.- Microcystin M180262.

GPS: 52.73623, -114.73663. Air Temp: 24 degC. Wind Speed: 5 km/h. Wind Direction: NE. Waves: 0m. -- Clam day, other boaters fishing. Water levels are low, barely reach boat launch. Apparently they pump water out of the east side of the lake. in area : campground (PP) logging industry. Microcystin ID M180261. Tow net.

GPS: 52.73617, -114.73645. Air Temp: 19 degC. Wind Speed: 10km/h. Wind Direction: N. Waves: 0.1 m. -- nice calm day. lots of mist this morning, rain the last couple of nights.  other boats fishing. lake has proper boat launch. Some people also dock their boat on shore near their campsite. Small fishing boats and zodiaks. 12 km/h spped limit on lake. Mirocystin ID: M180260. Tow net.

GPS: 52.73610, -114.73634. Air Temp: 10 degC. Wind Speed: 2 km/h. Wind Dir: NW. Waves: 0. -- Rainy day. yesterday big wind. 25 km/h - 30 km/h. Profile depth off 4 cm. 1 fishing boat, 1 kayak, 1 paddle board on lake today. Water levels still low on boat launch. Not sure if 7.5 m is bottom due to redox. line was still tight. ie not slack till 7.66 m. some cyano streaks near dock. Milfoil, pondweed, lilys by dock. Took grab smaple of cyano. Microcystin ID M. 180259. Tow net.

GPS: 52.7361, -114.736. Air Temp: -4 degC. Wind Speed 9 km/h. Wind Direction: W. Waves: 0.05 m. -- Quiet day, snow outside. Campground empty. Brown color to water, although can still see algae floating. At dock, algae clumps floating around 2 inches in size. Back in the lab, grab sample of grouped algae broke down. Turns out it was just aphanizomenon. Didn't send ot lab in the end. Microcystin ID: M 180258. Tow Net.

GPS: 54.28741. -111.10275. Air Temp: 26 degC. Wind Speed: 0 km/h. Wind Dir: NA. - Microcystin M180143. -- Water is up 18 inches this year. Mule deer X2. Slight algal blooms, some clumps, water clear, great blue heron, pelicans, paddle board person. . -- Microcystin M:180143

GPS: 54.28741, -111.10275. Air Temp: 21 degC. Wind Speed: 3-10 km/h. Wind Direction: NW. Waves: 0.1 m. -- Light wind, 4 loons, wind gusts to 12 km.h. Few clumps of algae floating, but clear, boating and tubing on the lake (x4) , people swimming, great blue herons, brook stickleback at the dock. microcystin M180142. Tow Net.

GPS  54.28741, -111.10275. Air Temp: 24 degC. Wind Speed: 5-9 km/h. Wind Direction: W. Waves: - -- light wind, 2-5 km/h. took zoo from 19 m but looked like we hit bottom. redo at 18 m and same thing. might be algae in the sample. all 3 mussel samples look silty. Microcystin M180141. Tow net.
Missed trip due to volunteer unavailability

GPS 54.28741, -111.102745. Air Temp: 8 degC. Wind Speed: 0-15 km/h. Wind Direction: E. Wvaes: 0-0.1 m . -- Calm at profile site due to east wind, cold. good day to sample, use EC weather report. Discrete metal handgrab at 0.5m

GPS: 55.88333. -119.21667. Air Temp: 10 degC. Wind Speed: 15 km/h. Wind Dir: NW. Waves: 0.1 m. -- Steady 15 km/h wind w low waves. 1 fishing baot on lake. Foam at shoreline and some duckweed. Single surface aerator running. -- Microcystin M180267.

GPS: 55.88333, -119.21667. Air Temp: 25 degC. Wind Speed: 20 km/h. Wind Direction: NW. Waves: 0.05 m. -- Some floating aphanezomenon, but is dispersed. Duck weed at dock, no blue green at dock. installed ais substrate at boat launch dock. Tow net. Microcystin ID M: 180268.

GPS: 55.88333, -119.21667. Air Temp: 25 degC. Wind Speed: 15 km/h. Wind Direction: SW. Waves: 0.05 m. 4 cm long minnows at boat launch. Lots of duckweed, surveyor died and restarted itself right before 1 m check. drfted 15 m during profile. Lots of dispersed grass clippings algae (aphanizomenon?). Duck family from las ttrip is still here (mallards). Muskrats or small beaver swimming by boat launch.  Tow net. Microcystin ID: M180269.

GPS: 55.88333, -119.21667. Air Temp: 4 degC. Wind Speed 5 km/h. Wind Direction: NW. Waves: 0.05 m. -- Sampled at 2.5 m which = 1 m off bottom. small amount of dispersed aphanezomenon in water. lots of duckwee @ boat launch. microcystin ID M180186. Tow net.

GPS 54.52389. 110.49556. Air Temp: 20 degC. Wind Speed: 1-5 km/h. Wind Dir: SW. Waves: n/a. -- Light wind, loons, pelicans, clear sky, no boars, very peaceful. 1 haul per site. Great blue heron. 1 person and 1 boat waterskiing. Wind increased to 15 km/h at 12 pm. -- Microcystin M180230.

GPS 54.52389 -110.49556. Air Temp: 14degC. Wind Speed 2 km/h. Wind Dir: S. Waves: 0. -- Calm day, other day was very windy, rescheduled to today. One haul per site. Midge pupae casings on surface. GPS: 54.52389, -110.49556. Air Temp: 16 degC. Wind Speed 6-13 km/h. Wind Dir. SW. Waves: 0.1 m. Light wind, ron commented excess leeches at his dock. Investigate reasons with pauline. Great blue heron. Swimmers itch at Ron's place. Microcysitn ID: M180228. Tow net.

GPS: 54.52389, -110.49556. Air Temp: 8 degC. Wind Speed: 0-6 km/h. Wind Direction: W. Waves: 0m. -- Loons grebes, light wind. Brad sampling with us today. No glacial colour, horsehair worm, wind picked up throughout sampling. Micocystin ID: M180227
GPS 54.52389. -110.49556. Air Temp: 0 degC. Wind Speed 0-2 km/h. Wind Direction: S. Waves 0. -- Cool, over 45 loons on the lake. -- M180226.

Profile was straight down but depths varied 30 cm bc of waves. -- Microcystin M180130.

GPS: 53.01719. -114.03962. Air Temp: 23 degC. Wind Speed: 9 km/h. Wind Direction: NE. Waves: 0.4 m. -- Lots of plant growth. early for the season. Both rooted lgae and plankton. Saw dead ifsh floating at surface. Gleotrichia particles at surface - took a grab sample at profile site. Gleo particles in pelagic zone - streaks closer to shorelines. lots of winds and storms recently. Tow net. Microcystin ID: M180129.

GPS: 53.01713. -114.04008. Air Temp: 22 degC. Wind Speed: 8 km/h. Wind Dir: From East. Waves: calm. -- Smoky and hazy. Gleotrichia, aphanizomenon, and other cyano clumps found at profile site (streaks on surface) 4-5 dead fish  - same as last trip in July. Microcystin ID M180126. Tow net.

GPS: 53.01713. -114.04008. Air temp: 17 deC .Wind Speed: 5 kmh. Wind Dir: SW. Waves: 0.05 m. -- suspended algae in wtaer column. including gleotrichea. Small amount of rain just before arrival on lake, but sun came out by profile. Had 30-50 kmh winds yesterday. Microcystin ID: M180128. Tow net.

GPS: 53.01713 -114.04008. Air Temp: 5 degC. Wind Speed: NA. Wind Dir: NA. Waves: NA. Green layer - lawn clippings - on surface. Aphanizomenon bloom in pelagic zone. Across the whole lake. Lots of residents have taken their boats and docks out. Microcystin ID M180127. Tow net.

Wind 5km/hr out of the W, lots of smoke from forest fires. Dock and launch full of seagulls, lots of pelicans around also. Lots of Aphan around the lake and at profile site. Colunteer Cidny joined us for the sample.

GPS: 55.21722. -119.08778. Air Temp: 10 degC. Wind Speed: 5 km/h. Wind Direction: SW. Waves: 0.05 m. Grab sample. Floating green particulate algae. Lots of weeds at boat launch and all around the lake. Microcystin ID M180175. Tow net.

Missed Trip. Boat motor would not start. Water off of dock is very turbid. Can see freshwater shrimp swimming near dock. 1 cm in size. moderately heavy snow fall till 9:30, then slowly tapered to 0 snow and wind dropped. Air Temp: 0 degC. Wind Speed: 5-10 kmh. Wind Direction: NE. %Cloud: 100. Waves: 0.02 m.
cotton fluff and plant material on the surface of water
Cloudy and calm. Lots of clumping algae on surface. Pillows of foam along east shoreline.
Lots of globular algae in water column.  Windy and smoky.
Cool and windy.  Lots of algae in the water column.

GPS: 53.86667. -111.1. Air Temp: 13 degC. Wind Speed: 5 km/h. Wind Dir: NW. Waves: 0. Waves increased during the day to 0.2m. -- Calm water at 945, wind increased around 11:30 am. Launched from the east side campsite. One boat on lake. Bald eagle sighting in morning. Patchy cloud clover 50-100%. Microcystin M180148.

GPS: 53.86667, -111.1. Air Temp: 13 degC. Wind Speed: 12 km/h. Wind Dir: N. Waves: 0.2 m. -- Formation of algae present, substrate sampler deployed at campsite dock, will inform manager. Wind clamed down to 5-10 kmh at 11:30. No boats out, volunteers say fish not biting, no people here. Blue green algae AHS posted signs. Wisconsin net. Microcystin ID: m180147

GPS: 53.86667, -111.1. Air Temp: 25 degC. Wind Speed: 13 kmh. Wind Dir: N. Waves: 0.3 m. -- White caps but below 20 kmh, winds gusted nera end of sampling to 30 kmh. -- Microcystin ID M180145. Tow net.

GPS: 53.86667, -111.1. Air Temp: 20 degC. Wind speed: 0-15 kmh. Wind Direction: N. Waves: 0-0.2 m. -- Calm at profile site then wind picked up, substrate sampler line cut and missing. Veliger samples were slimy brown and plugged the paster. Campsite on ast side closed the boat launch. Too shallow. Line was cut - no sampler, south side dock. Microcystin ID M: 180144. Tow net.
Discrete metal handgrab at 0.5m

GPS: 54.64389. -112.70528. Air Temp: 12 degC. Wind Speed: 5 km/h. Wind Direction: WSW. Waves: 0.1 m. -- Cloudy water over the winter until now, low visibility, light brown colour. Wind is very cool, stayed 5-10 km;h. 2 hauls at each site. Tubing to 1.6 m. Loons, geese, redneck grebes. Water dropped 7 ft since 1998. No boats on the lake but lots of wake boats. Wisconsin net. Microcystin ID: M180133.

GPS: 54.64389. -112.70528. Air temp: 19 degC. Wind Speed: 6-13 km/h. Wind Dir: SW. Waves: 0.1m Light wind, calm, loons, mergansers, sunshine throughout sampling. Sampling with brad and orest. No boats out , 1 paddle boarder. Microcystin ID: M180132. Tow net.

GPS 54.64389, -112.70528. Air Temp: 18 degC. Wind Speed: 0-5 km/h. Wind Dir: N. Waves: 0.  Smokey, overcast, light wind, bald eagles, loons, grebes, water up by 4.5 inches.  Microcystin ID M: 180131. Tow net.
GPS: 54.64389, -112.70528. Air Temp: 11 degC. Wind Speed: 7-11 km/h. Wind Dir: SE. %Cloud: Smoke and 50%. Waves: 0.05 m. Smoke from BC fires. Tow net. Microcystin ID M180237
GPS: 54.64389, -112.70528. Air Temp: 8 degC. Wind Speed: 6-11 kmh. Wind Dir: SE. Waves: 0.1 m -- Sampled with brad, cold and rainy. Microcystin ID M180236. Tow net.
Discrete metal handgrab at 0.5m

GPS: 54.61472. -112.72806. Few boats out. Windy, few white caps but wind calmed. Could not find 10 m deep spot so went with 9.5 m. 1 boat out fishing, wind calm nw side of the lake. Wind calm 5-10 km/h at last 2 sites then gusts to 30 km on last site. Pulled a body of a 67 year old man from the lake this morning according to volunteer. -- Microcystin M180138.

GPS: 54.61472. -112.72806. Air Temp: 18 degC. Wind Speed: 13-20 km/h. Wind Direction: S. Waves: 0.1 m. calm at marc's dock, pelican here, forgot anchor went back to get it. Wind picked up to 30-40 kmh gusts but from south so did not affect our sampling after 11 am. 1 haul tubing. 1 boat on the lake. NW side. substrate sampler is at 54.60299, -112.70774  by the public boat launch front of dock. Wisconsin net. Micorcystin ID: M180137\

GPS: 54.61472, -112.72806. Air Temp: 16 degC. Wind Speed: 13 km/h. Wind Dir: N. Waves: 0.1 m. 2 volunteers, overcast. 1 waleye, 2 unknown fish dead photo and 0.5 m long. Wind calmed down to 5 kmh at 1430. Redox values were not uploaded into the database. probe hit sediment earlier that day on skeleton north and redox measurements are of for this lake-Lindsay Boucher. Microcystin ID: M180136. Tow net.
GPS: 54.61472. -112.72806. Air Temp: 5 degC. Wind Speed: 6 km/h. Wind Direction: SW. Waves: 0.1 m. Cool, windy, 2 volunteers, very green water at mewatha beach. - Microcystin ID M180135. Tow net.
GPS: 54.61472, -112.72806. Air Temp: 9 degC. Wind Speed: 0-5 kmh. Wind Dir: E. Waves: 0m. Cold and rainy, sampled with brad. Microcystin IDM 180134. Tow net.
Redox values were not uploaded into the database
Discrete metal handgrab at 0.5m

GPS: 55.10278. -117.53750. Air Temp: 26 degC. Wind Speed: none. Wind Direction: none. Waves: 0 m. -- Calm and sunny. Few other boats. Fish jumping. Small amounts of floating debris at profile site. Small filamentous algae in water column. -- Microcystin M180181.

GPS: 55.10278, -117.53750. Air Temp: 16 degC. Wind Speed: 12-20 km/h. Wind Dir: NW. Waves: 0.2 m. -- AIS Substrated intsalled at young's point boat launch dock july 11th. Had to pull up probe and just boat position at 7.5 m. profile depth. lots of aphnizomenon floating in water column. Algae substantially more dense at site 7 compared to profile at westside. Microcystin ID: m180182. Tow net.

GPS: 55.10278, -117.53750. Air Temp: 11 degC. Wind Speed: 5 kmh. Wind Dir: SW. %Cloud: 0 but smoky. waves: 0. -- clumping of algae at shore and 1 km out from shore, otherwise is widely dispersed near centre of lake. Clumps mostly. Has been very windy for majority of past 2 weeks. Hundreds of franklin gulls floating alll over. Streaks of same algae in east side of lake. -- Microcystin ID M180183. Tow net. Blue scum on rocks at boat launch. One tp qc done under lake name lake 24.

GPS: 55.10278, -117.53750. Air Temp: 5 degC. Wind Speed: 0 kmh. Wind Dir: 0. Waves: 0. Still lots of algae in water. Blanketings ome parts near profile. Aphanizomenon and algae blankets streaking high across most of the lake. Few gulls and grebes on lake. no boats until last site. docks pulled up today (3/4 of them).. Microcystin ID M180184. Tow net.

SampleComment: GPS: 52'21.188. -114'08.692. Air Temp: 26 degC. Wind Speed: 22 km/h. Wind Dir: E. Waves: 0.3 m. -- Windy day, drifted a bit on profile site and on euphotic hauls. lots of summer villages, few boaters today. Took secchi at site 4 as well, same secchi depth. Not lots of runoff this spring. Snow melt taken up by vegetation in catchement. Concern about nutrients being too low - volunteer Graeme worried that nutrients settle into the sediment. -- Microcystin M180247

GPS: 5235352, -114.14521. Air Temp: 17 degC. Wind Speed: 15 km/h. Wind Dir: NE. waves: 0.2 m. -- A bit of windy gusts, had to finish profile on different side of boat and redo 11 m and on . No other boaters, storm expected later today. Not much rain lately, water levels down 8 centimeters. since june trip. Microcystin ID: M180246. Tow net.

GPS: 52.35402 -114.14561. Air Temp: 27. Wind Speed: 10 km/h. Wind Dir; NW. Waves 0.15. -- Quiet day, lots of hot weather past week. Cooled off past 2 days. No rain last 24 hours. Took secchi at every site all betwen 4-5 m. Lots of boat traffic on aug long weekend. Notmuch boat traffic during the week.Sylvan Stewardship Society and munipaclity working on a management plan with an environment component. Potential to include water quality anlysis in that plan. There was ash fall yesterday from forest fires. Microcystin ID M 180245. Tow net.
Missed Trip. Volunteers unavailable. Cancelled due to weather, then rescheduled fo a later date which was cancelled due to unavailability.
Missed Trip. Volunteer sunavailable. No boat in water after long weekend.

SampleComment: Calm and cloudy. Some clumping algae, more in north end of lake.
Mass of algal colonies in water column. Some large pillows of foam along east shore.
Abundant algae in water column.   Air is thick with forest fire smoke.
Water is very green with clump of algae.

Sunny,clear day. Winds 5-10 km/hr out of NW. Waves 0.2m --Bathymetric map from Alberta Lakes Atlas incorrect, found deeper profile location based on 20 year old map from fisheries. Use this map moving forward. All coordinates logged on Chris Ware's GPS. Indigenous volunteer mentioned there had been a possible whitefish kill this year, a few dead whitefish were present at the boat launch. Two dead backswimmers were also spotted at profile location- possible winter kill?

Wind speed 10km/hr out of South but picked up during comp to 20-25km/hr. Waves 0.2-0.5m. Lots of Gleotrichia present at profile site, hot and sunny day. Boat launch over grown with macrophytes and very difficult to launch blue lund. Fabian was unable to join us for sampling.
Winds 0-5km/hr from NW, 100% cloud-hazy from smoke. Lots of Aphan throughout water column, starting to clump up. Winter kill over last winter. Out with the volunteer, Fabian.
Winds 10-15km/hr out of SW, waves 0.05m. Lots of Aphan in the water, nice day.

GPS: 54.11528, -111.34861. Air Temperature: 9 degC. Wind Speed: 1 km/h. Wind Direction: N. Waves: 0. Wind calm, 1 boat on the lake, sunny, wind increasing to 5-10 km/h during sampling. Caterpillars devastated aspen with an infestation to the water's edge. 2 hauls per site = 3 m. Water level up several feet in the last 2 years. Cormorants pelicans, and grebes. Access lake at Patrick's place. -- Microcystin M180097.

GPS: 54.11528, -111.34861. Air Temp: 22 degC. Wind Speed: 13-22 km/h. Wind Dir: S. Waves: 0.4 m. -- light white caps, do not come out with wind more than 20 kmh. Substrate sampler at dock 54.11623, 111.36313. Filamentous algae noted, 1 haul at 3 m. Checked for mussels at public boat launch. String and globs of algae on north side, very thick. A garder snake chased a frog, then went swimming. Wisconsin. Microcystin M 180096.
GPS: 54.11528, -111.34861. Air temp: 23 degC. Wind Speed: 2-5 km/h. Wind Dir: SW. Waves: 0. Globes of algae present, green. Microcystin ID M180095. Tow net.

GPS: 54.11528, -111.34861. Air Temp: 16 degC. Wind Speed: 0. Wind Dir. 0. Waves: 0. Depth not correct to start. 23.5 m reading off at first, tried to calibrate to 1 m.
